&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director of System Support &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director for System Support is a key member of the System Transformation senior leadership team. This role is responsible for providing national level strategic leadership and direction for supporting systems as they transition to becoming Integrated Care Systems (ICSs). Crucially this role leads the development of systems to meet the needs of the emerging new operating model for the NHS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director is responsible for working across national and regional NHSEI teams and external experts to bring national best practice to systems and leading a team to provide hands-on support to deliver these changes. This hands-on support is done with and through regions, and is a combination of direct support into STPs and the development and delivery of at-scale support offers to a number of systems simultaneously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will demonstrate significant experience of leading a major system, regional or national programme of work. You will have demonstrable experience in a healthcare environment at local, national and regional levels with detailed knowledge of the health and care landscape, drawing on relationships across Whitehall, national bodies, the NHS and local government.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Matt Neligan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Director of System Transformation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: matt.nelgian@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
